  "body": "### Description\n\nI'm trying to configure quarkus to log exceptions with limited or no stacktrace, just the exception class and message, similar to logback's exception shortening (e.g. `%ex{short}`). \r\n\r\nI've tried changing the property:\r\n\r\n`quarkus.log.console.format=%d{yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss,SSS} %-5p [%c] (%t) %m%n`: logs message, exception and stacktrace\r\n`quarkus.log.console.format=%d{yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss,SSS} %-5p [%c] (%t) %s%e%n`: same as previous\r\n`quarkus.log.console.format=%d{yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss,SSS} %-5p [%c] (%t) %s%n`: does not log anything related to the exception.\r\n\r\nCurrently, there's no such option in JBoss LogManager, so this is not supported.\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\n_No response_",
